This paper discusses the design and analysis of a protocol for device-to-device (D2D) communication with radio frequency energy harvesting (RFEH) and interference management. The main focus is on improving the spectral and energy efficiency of next-generation wireless networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of stochastic geometry and transmission coordination, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions the use of tools for evaluating network performance, which could be relevant to the sub-categories cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
